(window["webpackJsonp"]=window["webpackJsonp"]||[]).push([["chunk-2d0db2c5"],{"6f76":function(a){a.exports=JSON.parse('{"title":"The Holy Name and The ten offences to be avoided","code":"en-HolyNameandThetenoffencestobeavoided","chapters":[{"title":"","paragraphs":[{"class":"b34","text":"\\r"},{"class":"b35","text":" All Glory to the Divine Master<br />and the Supreme Lord Śrī Kṛṣṇa Chaitanya"},{"class":"b36","text":" The Holy Name<br />&<br />The ten offences to be avoided"},{"class":"b37","text":" Āchāryyadev Oṁ Viṣṇupād Jagad-Guru<br />Aṣṭottara-śata-Śrī-Śrīmad"},{"class":"b73","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">Śrīla Bhakti Sundar Govinda Dev-Goswāmī Mahārāj</span>"},{"class":"b38","text":" Śrī Chaitanya Sāraswat Maṭh, Nabadwīp"}]},{"title":"Contents","paragraphs":[{"class":"b46","text":"\\r"},{"class":"b47","text":" Contents"},{"class":"b48","text":" <span class=\\"e1\\">The Holy Name & The ten offences to be avoided</span>"},{"class":"b48","text":" <span class=\\"e1\\">Daśa-vidha Nāmāparādha</span>"},{"class":"b48","text":" <span class=\\"e1\\">The Ten Offences to the Holy Name</span>"},{"class":"b48","text":" <span class=\\"e1\\">Śrī-Guru-Praṇāma-Mantra</span>"},{"class":"b49","text":" <span class=\\"e1\\">The Holy Name and The ten offences to be avoided, sixth edition</span>"}]},{"title":"The Holy Name&amp;The ten offences to be avoided","paragraphs":[{"class":"b46","text":"\\r"},{"class":"b47","text":" The Holy Name<br />&<br />The ten offences to be avoided"},{"class":"b50","text":" The Exalted <span class=\\"e3\\">Mantra</span> of the Five-fold Aspects of Śrī Chaitanyadev—"},{"class":"b60","text":" Śrī Kṛṣṇa Chaitanya, Prabhu Nityānanda<br />Śrī Advaita-Gadādhara, Śrī Vāsādi Gaura-bhaktavṛnda"},{"class":"b50","text":" The Supreme <span class=\\"e3\\">Mantra</span> of the Holy Name of the Supreme Lord—"},{"class":"b60","text":" Hare Kṛṣṇa Hare Kṛṣṇa Kṛṣṇa Kṛṣṇa Hare Hare<br />Hare Rama Hare Rama Rama Rama Hare Hare"},{"class":"b50","text":" The Divine Name’s Own Form—"},{"class":"b60","text":" nāma-chintāmaṇiḥ kṛṣṇaś-chaitanya-rasa-vigrahaḥ<br />pūrṇaḥ śuddho nitya-mukto ’bhinnatvān-nāma-nāminoḥ"},{"class":"b43","text":" As the Lord and His Name<br />are one and the same,<br />the Name is Kṛṣṇa Himself;<br />eternally pure, beyond the mundane,<br />Life, Joy and Love, full and complete,<br />sweet Holy Name,<br />wish-fulfilling Gem Divine."},{"class":"b69","text":" <span class=\\"e3\\">[Padma-Purāṇa]</span>"},{"class":"b50","text":" The Glories of the Holy Name—"},{"class":"b60","text":" harer nāma harer nāma harer nāmaiva kevalam<br />kalau nāsty eva nāsty eva nāsty eva gatir anyathā"},{"class":"b43","text":" The Holy Name, the Holy Name, the Holy Name alone—in this age of Kali there is no other shelter, no other shelter, no other shelter."},{"class":"b69","text":" <span class=\\"e3\\">[Bṛhan-Nāradīya-Purāṇa]</span>"},{"class":"b60","text":" hare keśava govinda vāsudeva jaganmaya<br />itīrayanti ye nityaṁ na hi tān bādhate kaliḥ"},{"class":"b43","text":" The influence of Kali no longer affects one who constantly chants the Holy Names of the Lord, such as Hare, Keśava, Govinda, Vāsudeva."},{"class":"b69","text":" <span class=\\"e3\\">[Bṛhan-Nāradīya-Purāṇa]</span>"},{"class":"b60","text":" kaler doṣa-nidhe rājannasti hy eko mahān guṇaḥ<br />kīrttanād eva kṛṣṇasya mukta-bandhaḥ paraṁ vrajet"},{"class":"b43","text":" O King, this age of Kali is a reservoir of inauspiciousness, yet it has but one glorious quality: in this age, simply by chanting the Holy Name of Śrī Kṛṣṇa, the soul is freed from the bondage of Māyā and attains to the shelter of the Lord Himself."},{"class":"b69","text":" <span class=\\"e3\\">[Śrīmad-Bhāgavatam 12.3.51]</span>"},{"class":"b50","text":" Even the sins of previous births are destroyed by taking the Holy Name of the Lord—"},{"class":"b60","text":" yan-nāma-dheyaṁ mriyamāṇa āturaḥ<br />patan skhalan vā vivaśo gṛṇan pumān<br />vimukta-karmmārgala uttamāṁ gatiṁ<br />prāpnoti yaṣyanti na taṁ kalau janāḥ"},{"class":"b43","text":" Even a person who is stumbling and falling, afflicted on the brink of death and helplessly passing away from the world—if he somehow takes the Holy Name of the Lord he is liberated from the bondage of <span class=\\"e3\\">karmma</span> and attains to the Supreme Destination. Alas! The fools of Kali-yuga have no desire to worship that Supreme Lord."},{"class":"b69","text":" <span class=\\"e3\\">[Śrīmad-Bhāgavatam 12.3.44]</span>"},{"class":"b60","text":" mahāpātaka-yukto ’pi kīrttayann aniśam harim<br />śuddhāntaḥkaraṇo bhūtvā jāyate paṅkti-pāvanaḥ"},{"class":"b43","text":" If the greatest sinner constantly chants the Holy Name, his heart becomes purified and he attains to the status of the twice-born."},{"class":"b69","text":" <span class=\\"e3\\">[Brahmāṇḍa-Purāṇa]</span>"},{"class":"b60","text":" etat ṣaḍ-varga-haraṇaṁ ripu-nigrahaṇaṁ param<br />adhyātma-mūlam etadd hi viṣṇor nāmānukīrtanam"},{"class":"b43","text":" Constantly chanting this Holy Name of Visnu is the root cause for destroying the forces of birth, death and the transformations of the body, and conquering the six terrible enemies, that is, lust, anger, greed, illusion, insanity and envy. It is the root of transcendental self-knowledge."},{"class":"b69","text":" <span class=\\"e3\\">[Skanda-Purāṇa]</span>"},{"class":"b50","text":" The Holy Name gives all the opportunity the reach Vaikuntha—"},{"class":"b60","text":" sarvvatra sarvva-kāleṣu ye ’pi kurvvanti pātakam<br />nāma-saṅkīrttanaṁ kṛtvā yānti viṣṇoḥ paraṁ padam"},{"class":"b43","text":" By the power of <span class=\\"e3\\">Nāma-saṅkīrttana</span> even a compulsive and habitual sinner can be purified and attain to the Supreme Abode of Lord Visnu."},{"class":"b69","text":" <span class=\\"e3\\">[Nandi-Purāṇa]</span>"},{"class":"b43","text":" Chanting the Holy Name is both the means and end for all—"},{"class":"b60","text":" etan nirvidyamānānām ichchhatām akutobhayam<br />yoginām nṛpa nirnitam harer nāmānukīrttanam"},{"class":"b43","text":" O King, the continuous hearing, chanting and remembering of the Supreme Lord’s Divine Name and Qualities has been ascertained by the previous Āchāryyas to be the Supreme means <span class=\\"e3\\">(sādhana)</span> and end <span class=\\"e3\\">(sādhya)</span> for all—whether those desiring enjoyment, heaven, liberation, etc., the self-satisfied <span class=\\"e3\\">yogīs,</span> or the exclusive devotees who are naturally indifferent to the world."},{"class":"b69","text":" <span class=\\"e3\\">[Śrīmad-Bhāgavatam 2.1.1]</span>"},{"class":"b50","text":" The last word of the Great Śrīmad-Bhāgavatam—"},{"class":"b60","text":" nāma-saṅkīrttanaṁ yasya sarvva-pāpa-praṇāśanam<br />praṇāmo duḥkha-śamanas taṁ namāmi harim param"},{"class":"b43","text":" I bow unto the Supreme Personality of Godhead Śrī Hari, by the congregational chanting of whose Name all sins are destroyed, and by offering obeisances unto whom all sorrow is dispelled."},{"class":"b69","text":" <span class=\\"e3\\">[Śrīmad-Bhāgavatam 12.13.23]</span>"},{"class":"b60","text":" idam eva hi māṅgalyam etad eva dhanārjjanam<br />jīvitasya phalaṁ chaitad yad dāmodara-kīrttanam"},{"class":"b43","text":" This chanting of the Divine Name of Dāmodara is the only auspiciousness, the only wealth and the only fulfillment of life."},{"class":"b69","text":" <span class=\\"e3\\">[Padma-Purāṇa]</span>"},{"class":"b50","text":" The Vedic Scriptures declare that the Holy Name holds the highest position of Transcendental Wisdom—"},{"class":"b60","text":" oṁ āsya jānanto nāma chid viviktan<br />mahas te viṣṇo sumatiṁ bhajāmahe<br />oṁ tat sat oṁ padaṁ devasya namasā vyantaḥ<br />śravasyavaśrava āpannam ṛk tam<br />nāmāni chiddadhire yajñiyāni<br />bhadrāyante raṇayantaḥ saṁdṛṣṭau<br />oṁ tam u stotāraḥ pūrvvaṁ yathāvida<br />ṛtasya garbhaṁ januṣā piparttana<br />āsya jānanto nāma chid viviktan<br />mahas te viṣṇo sumatiṁ bhajāmahe"},{"class":"b43","text":" “O Viṣṇu, since all the <span class=\\"e3\\">Vedas</span> are born from it, this Holy Name of Yours is Your living Divine Form, the illuminator of all that be; Your Name is the Supreme Ecstasy and the Divinity’s Own Form, approachable by all, and the Embodiment of Transcendental Wisdom—thus contemplating this Holy Name, non-different from You, we chant it again and again, worship and adore it.”"},{"class":"b44","text":" “O Viṣṇu, with our undivided concentration upon You, we wish to behold Your Transcendental Self, so we bow down again and again to Your dancing Lotus Feet, of inconceivable Potency, that purify Your devotees; we hear Your glorious renown sung in all four directions, and constantly singing Your Glories amongst us we have taken shelter of Your Transcendental, all-auspicious and worshippable Holy Names.”"},{"class":"b44","text":" [i] “Oh! You know that all-renowned Original Supreme Personality of Godhead to be Śrī Kṛṣṇa, so sing His Glories accordingly. He is clearly the Objective of the <span class=\\"e3\\">Vedas,</span> the concentrated Form of Eternity, Consciousness and Bliss. By chanting His unending Glories your life will be successful.”"},{"class":"b44","text":" [ii] “Fully describe the Transcendental Qualities of the Lord who appears in many Incarnations.”"},{"class":"b44","text":" [iii] “To our best capacity, we constantly sing Your unending Glories, making our lives successful. We have clearly concluded that Your Holy Name is Super-eminent, above everything—Your all-conscious Divine Form, the illuminator of all that be, the Supreme Ecstasy, approachable by all; thus, we, in Your Transcendental Service, continually chant Your Holy Name.”"},{"class":"b69","text":" <span class=\\"e3\\">[Hari-Bhakti-Vilās 11.274-276, Vedic Scriptural quote]</span>"},{"class":"b50","text":" The Holy Name is the Essence of the <span class=\\"e3\\">Vedas</span> and the worshippable objective of the liberated souls—"},{"class":"b60","text":" nikhila-śruti-mauli-ratna-mālā-dyuti-nīrājita-pāda-paṅkajānta<br />ayi mukta-kulair upāsyamāna paritas tvāṁ hari-nāma saṁśrayāmi"},{"class":"b43","text":" The Crown of all the <span class=\\"e3\\">Vedas</span>—the garland of jewels that is the Upaniṣads—eternally worship, by their brilliance (as an Ārati ceremony), the tips of the toes of Thy Lotus Feet. O Holy Name, Thou art ever worshipped by the great liberated souls (Nārada, Śuka and others, who are completely free from all mundane desires). So in every time, place and circumstance, O Name Divine, I surrender unto Thee."},{"class":"b69","text":" <span class=\\"e3\\">[Śrī Nāmāṣṭakam, śloka 1, Śrīla Rūpa Goswāmī]</span>"},{"class":"b50","text":" The Holy Name surpasses even the <span class=\\"e3\\">Vedas</span>—"},{"class":"b60","text":" mā ṛcho mā yajus tāta sāma paṭha kiñchana<br />govindeti harer nāma geyaṁ gāyasva nityaśaḥ"},{"class":"b43","text":" “O my beloved, you have no need to chant the prayers of such Scriptures as the <span class=\\"e3\\">Ṛk, Yajuḥ,</span> and <span class=\\"e3\\">Sāma Vedas.</span> You need only chant the Holy Names of the Lord like ‘Govinda,’ so please sing those Names always.”"},{"class":"b69","text":" <span class=\\"e3\\">[Skanda-Purāṇa]</span>"},{"class":"b43","text":" The Holy Name is superior even to all the Holy Places—"},{"class":"b60","text":" tīrtha-koṭi-sahasrāṇi tīrtha-koṭī-śatāni cha<br />tāni sarvvāṇy avāpnoti viṣṇor nāmāni kīrttanāt"},{"class":"b43","text":" Chanting the Holy Name of Lord Visnu awards one the fruit of serving billions of Holy Places of pilgrimage."},{"class":"b69","text":" <span class=\\"e3\\">[Vāmana-Purāṇa]</span>"},{"class":"b50","text":" To chant the Holy Name is the direct instruction of the Lord—"},{"class":"b60","text":" “prabhu bole—kahilaṅ ei mahāmantra<br />ihā japa giyā sabe kariyā nirbandha<br />ihā haite sarvva-siddhi haibe sabāra<br />sarvva-kṣaṇa bolo, ithe vidhi nāhi āra”"},{"class":"b43","text":" “The Lord said, ‘I have told you this <span class=\\"e3\\">Mahāmantra,</span> so everyone now chant it in proper measure. By doing this, you will attain success in all respects. There is no other rule but to chant it at every moment.’ ”"},{"class":"b69","text":" <span class=\\"e3\\">[Śrī Chaitanya-Bhāgavata Madhya 23.77-78]</span>"},{"class":"b60","text":" “ki śayane ki bhojane, ki vā jāgaraṇe<br />aharniśa chinta kṛṣṇa, boloho vadane”"},{"class":"b43","text":" “Whether resting, eating, or waking—day and night think of Kṛṣṇa and call His Name aloud.”"},{"class":"b69","text":" <span class=\\"e3\\">[Śrī Chaitanya-Bhāgavata Madhya 28.28]</span>"},{"class":"b60","text":" “aparādha-śūnya haye laha kṛṣṇa-nāma<br />kṛṣṇa mātā, kṛṣṇa pitā, kṛṣṇa dhana-prāṇa”"},{"class":"b43","text":" “Offencelessly go on taking the Holy Name of Kṛṣṇa; Kṛṣṇa is mother, Kṛṣṇa is father, Kṛṣṇa is our treasure, our life and soul.”"},{"class":"b69","text":" <span class=\\"e3\\">[Śrīla Bhaktivinoda Ṭhākur]</span>"},{"class":"b60","text":" “kali-kāle nāma-rūpe kṛṣṇa avatāra<br />nāma haite haya sarvva jagat nistāra”"},{"class":"b43","text":" In this age of Kali, Kṛṣṇa has incarnated in the Form of His Holy Name; through the chanting of the Holy Name, the whole world is delivered."},{"class":"b69","text":" <span class=\\"e3\\">[Śrī Chaitanya-Charitāmṛta Ādi 17.22]</span>"},{"class":"b60","text":" “nāma binā kali-kāle nāhi āra dharmma<br />sarvva-mantra-sāra nāma,—ei śāstra marmma”"},{"class":"b43","text":" “In this age of quarrel and hypocrisy there is no other religion but the chanting of the Holy Name; this is the essence of all <span class=\\"e3\\">Mantras,</span> this is the purport of all the Scriptures.”"},{"class":"b69","text":" <span class=\\"e3\\">[Śrī Chaitanya-Charitāmṛta Ādi 7.74]</span>"},{"class":"b60","text":" ‘‘kṛṣṇa-nāma bhaja jīva āra saba michhe<br />palāite patha nāi yama āche pichhe”"},{"class":"b43","text":" “O soul, serve the Divine Name of Lord Kṛṣṇa! All else is deception, and nothing else can save us from impending death.”"},{"class":"b69","text":" <span class=\\"e3\\">[Śrī Śrī Kṛṣṇera aṣṭottara-śata-nama]</span>"},{"class":"b50","text":" The different results of the pure Name, offence to the Name, and the twilight Name—"},{"class":"b60","text":" nāmaikaṁ yasya vāchi smarana-patha-gataṁ<br />śrotra-mūlaṁ gataṁ vā<br />śuddhaṁ vāśuddha-varṇaṁ vyavahita-rahitaṁ<br />tārayaty eva satyam<br />tach ched deha-draviṇa-janatā-lobha-<br />pāṣāṇa-madhye<br />nikṣipta syānn aphala-janakaṁ<br />śīghram evātra vipra"},{"class":"b43","text":" O <span class=\\"e3\\">brāhmaṇa,</span> if only one Holy Name of the Lord appears on one’s tongue, in the mind, or in the range of hearing, He [the Name] certainly delivers that person. Perfect or imperfect pronunciation or discrepancies in following the injunctions of the Scriptures do not effect the Potency of the Name. However, although the Name is full of all Divine Potencies, if we cast it upon the rocks of our mundane affairs such as body, house, wealth, society, greed, etc., He will not deliver His gracious reward immediately. [There are two kinds of obstacles—one lesser, one greater. In the case of the lesser, one may be not advancing on account of chanting <span class=\\"e3\\">Nāmābhāsa</span> or the “twilight Name”; whence the attainment of the fruit of chanting the Name may be delayed. But in the case of the greater, one chants <span class=\\"e3\\">Nāmāparādha,</span> offence to the Name, which can only be mitigated by continuously chanting the Name.]"},{"class":"b69","text":" <span class=\\"e3\\">[Padma-Purāṇa]</span>"},{"class":"b60","text":" nāmāparādha-yuktānāṁ nāmāny eva haranty agham<br />aviśrānta-prayuktāni tāny evārtha-karāṇi cha"},{"class":"b43","text":" The Name itself dispels the offence of its offenders—if they chant it without cessation they can attain the proper result of chanting, which is <span class=\\"e3\\">Kṛṣṇa-Prema,</span> by the Grace of the Holy Name."},{"class":"b69","text":" <span class=\\"e3\\">[Padma-Purāṇa]</span>"},{"class":"b50","text":" Four kinds of ‘hazy’ chanting or <span class=\\"e3\\">Nāmābhāsa</span>—the twilight dawning of the Holy Name which occurs before offenceless chanting—"},{"class":"b60","text":" sāṅketyaṁ pārihāsyaṁ vā stobhaṁ helanam eva vā<br />vaikuṇṭha-nāma-grahaṇam aśeṣāgha-haraṁ viduḥ"},{"class":"b43","text":" A person might chant the Name when (1) addressing another whose name is a name of the Lord, (2) in jest, (3) singing or in conversation, or even (4) without proper care or faith—yet, by somehow taking the Name of the Unlimited Supreme Lord, endless sins are destroyed; this fact is known to those learned in the Scriptures."},{"class":"b69","text":" <span class=\\"e3\\">[Śrīmad-Bhāgavatam 6.2.14]</span>"},{"class":"b60","text":" haridāsa kahen,—yaichhe sūryyera udaya<br />udaya nā ārambha tamera haya kṣaya<br />chaura-preta-rākṣasādit bhaya haya nāśa<br />udaya haile dharmma-karmma-ādi parakāśa<br />aichhe nāmodayārambhe pāpa-ādira kṣaya<br />udaya kaile kṛṣṇa-pade haya premodaya"},{"class":"b50","text":" Haridās said, “At twilight, the dispelling of darkness begins before the sun has risen. The fear of thieves, ghosts and evil forces is also dispelled; and when the sun has fully risen the nature and movement of things becomes revealed. Similarly, with the initial or twilight appearance of the Holy Name, our sins and obstacles are dispelled; and when the sun of the Holy Name rises fully, Love for the Divine Lotus Feet of the Lord awakens within the heart.”"},{"class":"b60","text":" avaśenāpi yan nāmni kīrttite sarvva-pātakaiḥ<br />pumān vimuchyate sadyaḥ siṁha-trastair mṛgair iva"},{"class":"b43","text":" As deer flee in fear of the roar of the lion, all sins immediately flee from one who chants the Holy Name, even by chance."},{"class":"b69","text":" <span class=\\"e3\\">[Garuḍa-Purāṇa]</span>"},{"class":"b60","text":" jayati jayati nāmānanda-rūpaṁ murārer<br />viramita-nija-dharmma-dhyāna-pūjādi-yatnam<br />katham api sakṛd āttaṁ muktidaṁ prāṇināṁ yat<br />paramam amṛtam ekaṁ jīvanaṁ bhūṣaṇaṁ me"},{"class":"b43","text":" Forever and ever, all Glory to the Embodiment of Ecstasy, the Holy Name of Murāri. Through chanting that Holy Name, we lose all interest in our attempts at conditional religion <span class=\\"e3\\">(varṇāśrama- dharmma),</span> meditation and worship. Even if this Name is somehow chanted only once (hazily or as <span class=\\"e3\\">Nāmābhāsa</span>}, it grants liberation to the living beings; it is the exclusive Supreme Nectar, it is my life, it is my most precious jewel."},{"class":"b69","text":" <span class=\\"e3\\">[Bṛhad-Bhāgavatāmṛtam 1.1.9]</span>"},{"class":"b50","text":" The slightest glimmer of the twilight Name is infinitely greater than all pious activities—"},{"class":"b60","text":" go-koṭi-dānaṁ grahaṇe bhagasya<br />prayāga-gaṅgodaka-kalpa-vāsaḥ<br />yajñāyutaṁ meru-suvarṇa-dānaṁ<br />govinda-kīrtter na samaṁ śatāṁśaiḥ"},{"class":"b43","text":" Making a gift of ten million cows on a solar eclipse, residing for a millennium at holy places, like Prayāg, where the sacred Ganges flows, performing ten thousand sacrifices and giving away a mountain of gold—hundreds of such pious activities can ever equal the slightest attempt to sing the Holy Name of the Supreme Lord Govinda."},{"class":"b69","text":" <span class=\\"e3\\">[Skanda-Purāṇa]</span>"},{"class":"b60","text":" jaya nāmadheya! munivṛnda-geya!<br />jana-rañjanāya paramākṣarākṛte!<br />tvam anādarād api manāg udīritam<br />nikhilogra-tāpa-paṭalīṁ vilumpasi"},{"class":"b43","text":" All Glory to You, O Holy Name! You are eternally sung by the sages; You are the joy of the hearts of all, and You have graciously appeared in this form of the Transcendental syllables to bring all good to the souls suffering in this world. If even without proper devotion a person just once calls out to You in his time of need, by Your slightest appearance all the terrible sins accumulated in the form of the mundane subtle body are destroyed in a split-second."},{"class":"b69","text":" <span class=\\"e3\\">[Śrī Nāmāṣṭakam, śloka 2, Śrīla Rūpa Goswāmī]</span>"},{"class":"b60","text":" madhura-madhuram etan maṅgalaṁ maṅgalānāṁ<br />sakala-nigama-vallī-sat-phalaṁ chit-svarūpam<br />sakṛd api parigītaṁ śraddhayā helayā vā<br />bhṛguvara nara-mātraṁ tārayet kṛṣṇa-nāma"},{"class":"b43","text":" Of all that is good,<br />this Name is its goodness.<br />Of all that is sweet,<br />this Name is its sweetness.<br />The Vedas are a vine<br />bearing nectarine fruit,<br />and that fruit divine<br />is this Holy Name."},{"class":"b44","text":" O best of the Bhārgavas,<br />know it for sure,<br />from the heart who does sing<br />Kṛṣṇa’s Name but just once,<br />innocently, without offence,<br />no matter their mind,<br />whether faithful or casual,<br />the Lord’s Name will save all<br />from suffering eternal."},{"class":"b69","text":" <span class=\\"e3\\">[Skanda-Purāṇa]</span>"},{"class":"b50","text":" A revelation of the Lord’s affection for His devotee, through the Grace of His Holy Name—"},{"class":"b60","text":" ṛṇam etat pravṛddhaṁ me hṛdayān nāpasarpati<br />yad govindeti chukrośa kṛṣṇa māṁ dūravāsinam"},{"class":"b43","text":" “Feeling My separation, Draupadī called out to Me, ‘Oh Govinda’, and I have become more and more indebted to her for that; so much so, that the memory of it never leaves My heart.”"},{"class":"b69","text":" <span class=\\"e3\\">[Mahābhārata]</span>"},{"class":"b50","text":" Chanting the Holy Name is successful in the association of the true devotees—"},{"class":"b60","text":" “asādhu-saṅge bhāi, kṛṣṇa-nāma nāhi haya<br />nāmākṣara bāhirāya baṭe, tabu nāma kabhu naya<br />kabhu nāmābhāsa haya, sadā nāma-aparādha<br />esaba jānibe, bhāi, kṛṣṇa-bhaktira bādha<br />yadi karibe kṛṣṇa-nāma, sādhu-saṅga kara<br />bhukti-mukti-siddhi-vāñchhā dūre parihara<br />‘daśa-aparādha’ tyaja māna-apamān<br />anāsaktye viṣaya bhuñja āra laha kṛṣṇa-nām<br />kṛṣṇa-bhaktir anukūl sab karaha svīkār<br />kṛṣṇa-bhaktir pratikūl sab kara parihār”<br />“baddha-jīve kṛpā kari’ kṛṣṇa haila nām<br />kali-jīve dayā kari’ kṛṣṇa haila gaura-dhām<br />ekānta sarala-bhāve bhaja gaura-jan<br />tabe ta’ pāibe, bhāi, śrī-kṛṣṇa-charaṇ<br />gaura-jana saṅga kara gaurāṅga baliyā<br />‘hare kṛṣṇa’ nām bolo nāchiyā nāchiyā<br />achire pāibe bhāi nāma-prema-dhan<br />yāhā bilāite prabhur nade’ āgaman”"},{"class":"b43","text":" “But you cannot obtain the Name of Kṛṣṇa without the company of the saintly devotees; one may chant superficially—the syllables of the Name may be present, but not the Name proper. Chanting without devotional association may at best be a ‘hazy’ aspect of the Name <span class=\\"e3\\">(Nāmābhāsa),</span> but offence to the Name <span class=\\"e3\\">(Nāmāparādha)</span> is inevitable."},{"class":"b44","text":" “Dear brother, you must be aware that these things are obstacles to Devotion for Lord Kṛṣṇa. So if you want to take the Holy Name of the Lord, take the association of the pure and saintly true devotee, and cast out from your heart all desires for exploitation <span class=\\"e3\\">(karmma), </span>liberation <span class=\\"e3\\">(jñāna)</span> and mystic powers <span class=\\"e3\\">(siddhis</span>).”"},{"class":"b44","text":" “Cast away the ten offences, forget your honour or dishonour, take only what you need in this world to keep body and soul together and go on chanting the Holy Name of Kṛṣṇa. Accept all that is favorable for Devotion to Kṛṣṇa, abandon all that is unfavorable."},{"class":"b44","text":" “Being gracious to the conditioned souls, Kṛṣṇa appears in the Form of His Holy Name. Being merciful to the souls of Kali, He came as the Abode of all Transcendental Qualities, Śrī Gaurasundar. So with all your sincerity, serve the beloved ones of Gaura. Then, my brother, you will reach the Lotus Feet of Śrī Kṛṣṇa."},{"class":"b44","text":" Associate with the devotees of Gaura, sing the Name of Gaura, chant ‘Hare Kṛṣṇa’ and dance. Very soon, my friend, you’ll receive the golden gift of Divine Love; and that’s why Prabhu came here to Nadīyā—to give that to you.”"},{"class":"b69","text":" <span class=\\"e3\\">[Prema-vivartta]</span>"},{"class":"b50","text":" The ten offences to be avoided, as taught by the Scriptural Word of the <span class=\\"e3\\">Padma-Purāṇa</span>—"},{"class":"b43","text":" (1) satāṁ nindā nāmnaḥ param aparādhaṁ vitanute<br />yataḥ khyātiṁ yātaṁ katham u sahate tad vigarhām"},{"class":"b44","text":" (2) śivasya śrī-viṣṇor ya iha guṇa-nāmādi-sakalaṁ<br />dhiyā bhinnaṁ paśyet sa khalu harināmāhita-karaḥ"},{"class":"b44","text":" (3) guror avajñā (4) śruti-śāstra-nindanam"},{"class":"b44","text":" (5) tathārthavādo (6) harināmni kalpanam"},{"class":"b44","text":" (7) nāmno balād yasya hi pāpa-buddhir<br />na vidyate tasya yamair hi śuddhiḥ"},{"class":"b44","text":" (8) dharmma-vrata-tyāga-hutādi-sarvva-<br />śubha-kriyā-sāmām api pramādaḥ"},{"class":"b44","text":" (9) aśraddadhāne vimukhe ’py aśṛṇvati<br />yaś chopadeśaḥ śiva-nāmāparādhaḥ"},{"class":"b52","text":" (10) śrute ’pi nāma-māhātmye yaḥ prīti-rahito naraḥ<br />ahaṁ mamādi paramo nāmni so ’py aparādha-kṛt"}]},{"title":"Daśa-vidha Nāmāparādha","paragraphs":[{"class":"b46","text":"\\r"},{"class":"b47","text":" Daśa-vidha Nāmāparādha"},{"class":"b60","text":" hari-nāma mahāmantra sarvva-mantra-sāra<br />yādera karuṇābale jagate prachāra<br />sei nāma-parāyana sādhu, mahājana<br />tāhādera nindā nā kariha kadāchana [1]"},{"class":"b60","text":" vrajendranandana kṛṣṇa sarvveśvareśvara<br />maheśvara ādi tāra sevana-tatpara<br />nāma chintāmani kṛṣṇa-chaitanya-svarūpa<br />bheda-jñāna nā karibe līlā-guṇa-rūpa [2]"},{"class":"b60","text":" “guru kṛṣṇa-rūpa han śāstrera pramāṇe<br />guru-rūpe kṛṣṇa kṛpā kare bhāgyavāne”<br />se gurute marttya-buddhi avajñādi tyaji<br />iṣṭa-lābha kara, nirantara nāma bhaji [3]"},{"class":"b60","text":" śruti, śruti-mātā-saha sātvata-purāṇa<br />śrī-nāma-charaṇa-padma kare nīrājana<br />sei śruti-śāstra yebā karaye nindana<br />se aparādhīra saṅga karibe varjjana [4]"},{"class":"b60","text":" nāmera mahimā sarvva-śāstrete vākhāne<br />atistuti, hena kabhu nā bhāviha mane<br />agastya, ananta, brahmā, śivādi satata<br />ye nāma-mahimā-gāthā saṅkīrttana-rata<br />se nāma-mahimā-sindhu ke pāibe pāra?<br />atistuti bale yei—sei durāchāra [5]"},{"class":"b60","text":" kṛṣṇa-nāmāvalī nitya golokera dhana<br />kalpita, prākṛta, bhāve—aparādhī jana [6]"},{"class":"b60","text":" nāme sarvva-pāpa-kṣaya sarvva-śāstre kaya<br />sārā-dina pāpa kari sei bharasāya—<br />emata durbbuddhi yāra sei aparādhī<br />māyā-pravañchita, duḥkha bhuñje niravadhi [7]"},{"class":"b60","text":" atulya śrī-kṛṣṇa-nāma pūrṇa-rasa-nidhi<br />tāra sama nā bhāviha śubha-karmma ādi [8]"},{"class":"b60","text":" nāme śraddhā-hīna-jana—vidhātā vañchita<br />tāre nāma dāne aparādha suniśchita [9]"},{"class":"b60","text":" śuniyāo kṛṣṇa-nāma-māhātmya apāra<br />ye prīti-rahita, sei narādhama chhāra<br />ahaṁtā mamatā yāra antare bāhire<br />śuddha kṛṣṇa-nāma tāra kabhu nāhi sphure [10]"},{"class":"b60","text":" ei daśa aparādha kariyā varjjana<br />ye sujana kare harināma saṅkīrttana<br />apūrvva śrī-kṛṣṇa-prema labhya tāra haya<br />nāma-prabhu tāra hṛde nitya vilasaya [11]"}]},{"title":"The Ten Offencesto the Holy Name","paragraphs":[{"class":"b46","text":"\\r"},{"class":"b35","text":" All Glory to the Divine Master<br />and the Supreme Lord Śrī Kṛṣṇa Chaitanya"},{"class":"b47","text":" The Ten Offences<br />to the Holy Name"},{"class":"b42","text":" [to be carefully avoided by the devotee]"},{"class":"b35","text":" By His Divine Grace<br />Śrīla Bhakti Sundar Govinda Dev-Goswāmī Mahārāj"},{"class":"b43","text":" 1. Hare Kṛṣṇa Mahāmantra—<br />of all mantras the best,<br />Throughout the world is preached<br />by saints’ potent grace behest;<br />Such saints to the Name devoted,<br />such pure souls great:<br />Never dare offend them—<br />dare not show them hate."},{"class":"b44","text":" 2. Lord Kṛṣṇa, son of Nanda,<br />of all lords the Leader—<br />The great Śiva and all the gods<br />serve His feet forever;<br />The touchstone of the Name<br />is Kṛṣṇa incarnate—<br />His Pastimes, Nature, Form also<br />think not separate."},{"class":"b44","text":" 3. “Guru’s a form of Kṛṣṇa—<br />the Scriptures corroborate;<br />In the form of Guru,<br />Kṛṣṇa blesses the fortunate.”<br />Never offend that Guru<br />by thinking him mere mortal;<br />Gain your highest objective—<br />serve the Name for time eternal."},{"class":"b44","text":" 4. The Vedas with Mother Gāyattrī<br />and Śrīmad-Bhāgavatam<br />Illuminate the Lotus Feet<br />of Śrī Hari’s Name;<br />Whoever vilifies<br />those Holy Vedic Scriptures—<br />Never keep their company,<br />know them as offenders."},{"class":"b44","text":" 5. The Glories of the Name—<br />all Scriptures’ exaltation,<br />Dare not think their praise<br />to be exaggeration;<br />Agastya, Ananta, Brahmā,<br />Śiva, etc., ever<br />Sing the Glories of that Name<br />with full-hearted fervour.<br />Who can cross the ocean<br />of the Glories of that Name?<br />Whoever says ‘exaggeration’<br />have their sin to blame."},{"class":"b44","text":" 6. The Holy Names of Kṛṣṇa—<br />eternal wealth of Goloka:<br />Who thinks those Names imaginary,<br />mundane—he’s offender."},{"class":"b44","text":" 7. All Scriptures claim the Name<br />all sin it can destroy,<br />But those who spend their time in vain<br />making it a ploy—<br />Such a wicked attitude<br />is that of an offender<br />Drowning in delusion,<br />perpetually to suffer."},{"class":"b44","text":" 8. Incomparable Name of Kṛṣṇa—<br />the treasure of ecstasy:<br />Never dare compare it with<br />auspicious piety."},{"class":"b44","text":" 9. Those who’re faithless t’ward the Name—<br />deceived by Providence:<br />Giving them the Holy Name<br />surely’s an offence."},{"class":"b44","text":" 10. Despite them hearing the infinite<br />Glories of Kṛṣṇa’s Name,<br />Those whose hearts don’t melt in love are rascals of ill fame;<br />Only pride and avarice<br />their thoughts and words do yield—<br />The Pure Name of Kṛṣṇa<br />to them is ne’er revealed."},{"class":"b51","text":" 11. Casting off these ten offences,<br />leaving no exception,<br />Those pure souls who chant the Name<br />in Holy Congregation—<br />The miracle of Love for Kṛṣṇa<br />they will surely savour,<br />The Name Divine Himself will shine<br />within their hearts forever."},{"class":"b52","text":" <span class=\\"e3\\">—English translation of the original Bengali poem that was written on 2nd April, 1989 by His Divine Grace Śrīla Bhakti Sundar Govinda Dev-Goswāmī Mahārāj</span>"}]},{"title":"Śrī-Guru-Praṇāma-Mantra","paragraphs":[{"class":"b46","text":"\\r"},{"class":"b47","text":" Śrī-Guru-Praṇāma-Mantra"},{"class":"b60","text":" gurvābhīṣṭa-supūrakaṁ guru-gaṇair aśīṣa-saṁbhūṣitaṁ<br />chintyāchintya-samasta-veda-nipuṇaṁ śrī-rūpa-panthānugam<br />govindābhidham ujjvalaṁ vara-tanuṁ bhakty anvitaṁ sundaraṁ<br />vande viśva-guruṁ cha divya-bhagavat-premṇo hi bīja-pradam"},{"class":"b55","text":" He perfectly fulfills the deepest wishes of his Gurudev, He is splendidly adorned with the blessings of all his Gurus; adept in the perfect conclusions of all the <span class=\\"e3\\">Vedas,</span> both conceivable and inconceivable, He is the faithful follower in the Line of Śrīla Rūpa Goswāmī Prabhupāda; His Name is Śrīla Bhakti Sundar Govinda Dev-Goswāmī Mahārāj, of superexcellent charming Form so radiant to behold; His heart is filled with Pure Loving Devotion, He is the Divine Master of the whole creation, and the Gracious Bestower of the seed of Love Divine. Ever singing his Transcendental Glories, I offer my obeisances unto His Holy Lotus Feet."}]},{"title":"The Holy Name and The ten offences to be avoided, sixth edition","paragraphs":[{"class":"b46","text":"\\r"},{"class":"b47","text":" The Holy Name and The ten offences to be avoided, <span class=\\"e3\\">sixth edition</span>"},{"class":"b43","text":" In the Service of Oṁ Viṣṇupād Śrīla Bhakti Sundar Govinda Dev-Goswāmī Maharaj, our most beloved and revered Āchāryyadev who is mercifully carrying the Teachings of the Holy Name all over the world, fulfilling the Divine Wish of The Guardian of Devotion Oṁ Viṣṇupād Śrīla Bhakti Rakṣak Śrīdhar Dev-Goswāmī Mahārāj—"},{"class":"b44","text":" Translated, revised, amended and electronically published by Śrī Swarupananda Dasadhikari from London, 19th November, 2001, Holy Disappearance Day of the Merciful Distributor of Holy Name, His Divine Grace Śrīla Bhakti Vedānta Swāmī Mahārāj Prabhupāda."},{"class":"b51","text":" <span class=\\"e3\\">Acknowledgements: </span>Śrī Jaiva-Dharmma, Śrī Gauḍīya-Kaṇṭhahāra <span class=\\"e3\\">(Bengali/Sanskrit).</span>"},{"class":"b60","text":" śrī-svarūpa-rāya-rūpa-jīva-bhāva-sambharaṁ<br />varṇa-dharmma-nirvviśeṣa-sarvvaloka-nistaram<br />śrī-sarasvatī-priyaṁ cha bhakti-sundarāśrayaṁ<br />śrīdharaṁ namāmi bhakti-rakṣakaṁ jagad-gurum"},{"class":"b55","text":" I bow down unto the Guru of the entire world,<br />my Divine Master Oṁ Viṣṇupād<br />Śrīla Bhakti Rakṣak Śrīdhar Dev-Goswāmī Mahārāj.<br />He is the gracious carrier of the Conception<br />of Śrī Swarūpa, Śrī Rāmānanda, Śrī Rūpa and Śrī Jīva;<br />He is the Saviour of all, regardless of caste or creed;<br />He is the most beloved intimate servitor<br />of Śrīla Bhakti Siddhānta Saraswatī Goswāmī Prabhupāda.<br />He is the Supersubjective Potency (Āśraya-vigraha)<br />of the Sweetest Transcendental Devotion<br />(Parama Mādhuryyamaya Bhakti)<br />and the only shelter of<br />Śrī Bhakti Sundar Govinda Mahārāj."}]}]}')}}]);
